        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Weigh the water phase ingredients (oat milk and distilled water) into one heat-resistant bowl and heat to 70 degrees Celsius. In a separate bowl, weigh the oil phase ingredients (sweet almond oil, shea butter, emulsifying wax) and heat to 70 degrees Celsius until the emulsifying wax has fully melted.",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pour the water phase slowly into the oil phase while mixing continuously with a stick blender on low. The mixture will immediately begin to emulsify and turn white and creamy. Continue blending for 3 to 5 minutes until the lotion is homogeneous.",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Allow to cool to below 40 degrees Celsius. Add the glycerine, preservative, and lavender essential oil and stir to incorporate. Pour into a clean jar. Label with the date made.",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Storage and shelf life",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Store at room temperature, away from direct sunlight. Shelf life is 3 months with a broad-spectrum preservative. Discard if the lotion separates and does not re-combine with shaking, develops a sour or off smell, or shows any visible contamination. Use a pump dispenser or clean spatula to prevent introducing bacteria from fingers into the jar.",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
